imizing components — memoization, preventing re-renders |\n112: | `.claude/react/docs/security-best-practices.md` | Before handling user content — XSS prevention, dangerouslySetInnerHTML |\n113: | `.claude/react/docs/i18n-architecture.md` | Before adding i18n — react-i18next setup, locale files |\n114: | `.claude/react/docs/browser-testing.md` | Before writing browser tests — UI and API integration testing |\n115: \n116: ### Before Writing Backend Code\n117: \n118: Read these docs:\n119: \n120: | Doc | When to Read |\n121: |-----|-------------|\n122: | `.claude/nestjs/guides/architecture-overview.md` | Before creating ANY module — 4-layer pattern, base classes, main.ts |\n123: | `.claude/nestjs/guides/best-practices.md` | Before writing any backend code — coding standards, critical rules |\n124: | `.claude/nestjs/guides/nestjs-backend-guide.md` | General NestJS reference — navigation guide linking all detailed guides |\n125: | `.claude/nestjs/guides/routing-and-controllers.md` | Before writing controllers |\n126: | `.claude/nestjs/guides/services-and-repositories.md` | Before writing services |\n127: | `.claude/nestjs/guides/database-patterns.md` | Before writing entities |\n128: | `.claude/nestjs/guides/validation-patterns.md` | Before writing DTOs |\n129: | `.claude/nestjs/guides/authentication-cookies.md` | Before writing auth — JWT, httpOnly cookies, token rotation |\n130: | `.claude/nestjs/guides/setup-role-base-access.md` | Before implementing RBAC — roles, guards, JWT integration |\n131: | `.claude/nestjs/guides/async-and-errors.md` | Before writing async code — async/await patterns, error handling |\n132: | `.claude/nestjs/guides/middleware-guide.md` | Before writing middleware — guards, interceptors, pipes, exception filters |\n133: | `.claude/nestjs/guides/configuration.md` | Before managing config — UnifiedConfig pattern for env/secrets |\n134: | `.claude/nestjs/guides/update-swagger.md` | Before documenting APIs — Swagger decorators, DTO documentation |\n135: | `.claude/nestjs/guides/testing-guide.md` | Before writing tests — Jest patterns, mocking, best practices |\n136: | `.claude/nestjs/guides/sentry-and-monitoring.md` | Before adding monitoring — Sentry v8 error tracking, performance |\n137: | `.claude/nestjs/guides/workflow-convert-prd-to-knowledge.md` | Before converting PRD — structured PROJECT_KNOWLEDGE.md generation |\n138: | `.claude/nestjs/guides/workflow-design-database.md` | Before designing database — TypeORM + PostgreSQL schema design |\n139: | `.claude/nestjs/guides/workflow-generate-api-docs.md` | Before generating API docs — Markdown docs from controllers/DTOs |\n140: | `.claude/nestjs/guides/workflow-generate-e2e-tests.md` | Before generating e2e tests — test generation for controllers |\n141: | `.claude/nestjs/guides/workflow-implement-redis-caching.md` | Before adding caching — Redis with @Cacheable/@CacheInvalidate |\n142: \n143: ### Key Patterns (Do NOT Deviate)\n144: \n145: **Frontend:**\n146: - React Router 7 **framework mode** (NOT library mode, NOT `createBrowserRouter`)\n147: - Entry point: `root.tsx` (NOT `main.tsx`)\n148: - Route config: `routes.ts` with `route()`, `layout()`, `index()` from `@react-router/dev/routes`\n149: - Imports from `react-router` (NOT `react-router-dom`)\n150: - Route protection: inline RBAC in `ProtectedLayout` with `routeAccess` map\n151: - Auth pages: `GuestGuard` renders `<Outlet />` or redirects\n152: - Data fetching: Redux `createAsyncThunk` in service files (NOT TanStack Query)\n153: - Source directory: `app/` (NOT `src/`)\n154: - Import alias: `~/` (NOT `@/`)\n155: \n156: **Backend:**\n157: - NestJS 4-layer: Controller → Service → Repository → Entity\n158: - ALL layers extend base classes from `src/core/base/`\n159: - Guards, decorators, filters in `src/core/` (NOT inside feature modules)\n160: - JWT via httpOnly cookies (NEVER localStorage)\n161: - Repository pattern via TypeORM (NEVER query directly in services)\n162: \n163: ### Doc Reading Enforcement (MANDATORY)\n164: \n165: **NEVER generate code from memory.** You MUST read the referenced submodule doc using the Read tool and match its patterns EXACTLY before writing any code.\n166: \n167: Process:\n168: 1. Read the doc file with the Read tool (NOT from your training data)\n169: 2. Extract the specific class names, import paths, decorators, and file structures it defines\n170: 3. Use THOSE exact patterns in your code — not what you \"know\" about NestJS or React in general\n171: \n172: **Anti-patterns (these indicate you skipped reading the docs):**\n173: - Using `createBrowserRouter` or `<BrowserRouter>` → doc says: framework mode with `route()`\n174: - Using `@/` imports → doc says: `~/`\n175: - Using `src/` as source dir → doc says: `app/`\n176: - Putting guards inside feature modules → doc says: `src/core/`\n177: - Using TanStack Query → doc says: Redux `createAsyncThunk`\n178: - Using `react-router-dom` → doc says: `react-router`\n179: - Creating `main.tsx` entry point → doc says: `root.tsx`\n180: - Writing raw axios calls → doc says: use `httpMethods/` factories\n181: - Skipping base class extension → doc says: ALL layers extend base classes\n182: \n183: If you find yourself writing code that matches any anti-pattern above, STOP — you are generating from memory, not from the docs. Read the doc and correct your code.\n184: \n185: ---\n186: \n187: ## Tech Stack\n188: \n189: | Layer | Technology |\n190: |-------|------------|\n191: | Backend | {BACKEND} |\n192: | Frontend | {FRONTEND} |\n193: | Admin Dashboard | {ADMIN_DASHBOARD} |\n194: | Database | {DATABASE} |\n195: | ORM | {ORM} |\n196: | Authentication | {AUTH} |\n197: | Deployment | {DEPLOYMENT} |\n198: \n199: ---\n200: \n201: ## Project Structure\n202: \n203: ```\n204: {PROJECT_NAME}/\n205: ├── backend/                      # {BACKEND} API\n206: │   ├── src/\n207: │   │   ├── core/                # Base classes, guards, decorators, filters\n208: │   │   │   ├── base/            # BaseEntity, BaseRepository, BaseService, BaseController\n209: │   │   │   ├── decorators/      # @Public(), @Roles(), @CurrentUser()\n210: │   │   │   ├── guards/          # JwtAuthGuard, RolesGuard\n211: │   │   │   ├── filters/         # HttpExceptionFilter\n212: │   │   │   ├── interceptors/    # TransformInterceptor, LoggingInterceptor\n213: │   │   │   └── pipes/           # ValidationPipe\n214: │   │   ├── modules/             # Feature modules (entity, repo, service, controller, module)\n215: │   │   ├── infrastructure/      # External services (mail, s3, token, logging)\n216: │   │   └── database/            # Migrations, seeds\n217: │   └── test/                    # E2E tests\n218: ├── frontend/                    # {FRONTEND} user application\n219: │   └── app/                     # Source directory (NOT src/)\n220: │       ├── components/          # ui/, atoms/, modals/, shared/, layouts/, guards/\n221: │       ├── pages/               # Route pages\n222: │       ├── services/            # httpService.ts, httpMethods/, httpServices/\n223: │       ├── redux/               # features/, store/\n224: │       ├── types/               # .d.ts per domain\n225: │       ├── enums/               # Synced from backend\n226: │       ├── contexts/            # AuthContext\n227: │       ├── hooks/               # Custom hooks\n228: │       ├── lib/                 # cn() utility\n229: │       ├── utils/               # errorHandler, validations/\n230: │       └── styles/              # Tailwind + theme variables\n231: ├── frontend-admin-dashboard/    # Admin dashboard\n232: ├── .claude/                     # Claude Code configuration + submodule docs\n233: ├── .claude-project/             # Project documentation\n234: └── docker-compose.yml           # Docker configuration\n235: ```\n236: \n237: ---\n238: \n239: ## Git Rules\n240: \n241: - Branch from `dev`, PR to `dev`, never push directly to `main`\n242: - Branch naming: `feature/<name>`, `fix/<name>`, `chore/<name>`\n243: - Commit messages: imperative mood, concise, reference ticket if exists\n244: \n245: ---\n246: \n247: ## User Roles\n248: \n249: | Role | Description | Key Permissions |\n250: |------|-------------|-----------------|\n251: | Guest | Unauthenticated visitor | View public pages, Login, Signup |\n252: | {ROLE_1} | {ROLE_1_DESCRIPTION} | {ROLE_1_PERMISSIONS} |\n253: | {ROLE_2} | {ROLE_2_DESCRIPTION} | {ROLE_2_PERMISSIONS} |\n254: | Admin | Platform administrator | {ADMIN_PERMISSIONS} |\n255: \n256: ---\n257: \n258: ## Core Enums\n259: \n260: | Enum | Values |\n261: |------|--------|\n262: | RoleEnum | {ROLE_ENUM_VALUES} |\n263: | UserStatusEnum | `active`, `suspended` |\n264: \n265: ---\n266: \n267: ## Key Documentation\n268: \n269: | Document | Path | Description |\n270: |----------|------|-------------|\n271: | Project Knowledge | [.claude-project/docs/PROJECT_KNOWLEDGE.md](.claude-project/docs/PROJECT_KNOWLEDGE.md) | Core project info, features, roles |\n272: | API Documentation | [.claude-project/docs/PROJECT_API.md](.claude-project/docs/PROJECT_API.md) | API endpoints and specifications |\n273: | Database Schema | [.claude-project/docs/PROJECT_DATABASE.md](.claude-project/docs/PROJECT_DATABASE.md) | Entity definitions and relationships |\n274: | API Integration | [.claude-project/docs/PROJECT_API_INTEGRATION.md](.claude-project/docs/PROJECT_API_INTEGRATION.md) | Frontend-backend integration |\n275: \n276: ### Status Tracking\n277: \n278: | Status File | Path |\n279: |-------------|------|\n280: | Backend API Status | [.claude-project/status/backend/API_IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS.md](.claude-project/status/backend/API_IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS.md) |\n281: | Frontend Screens | [.claude-project/status/frontend/SCREEN_IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS.md](.claude-project/status/frontend/SCREEN_IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS.md) |\n282: | Frontend API Integration | [.claude-project/status/frontend/API_INTEGRATION_STATUS.md](.claude-project/status/frontend/API_INTEGRATION_STATUS.md) |\n283: \n284: ### Memory (Persistent Context)\n285: \n286: | File | Purpose |\n287: |------|---------|\n288: | [DECISIONS.md](.claude-project/memory/DECISIONS.md) | Architecture decisions log |\n289: | [LEARNINGS.md](.claude-project/memory/LEARNINGS.md) | Patterns and insights |\n290: | [PREFERENCES.md](.claude-project/memory/PREFERENCES.md) | Coding style preferences |\n291: \n292: ---\n293: \n294: ## API Base URLs\n295: \n296: | Environment | URL |\n297: |-------------|-----|\n298: | Development | `http://localhost:3000/api` |\n299: | Staging | `https://staging.{PROJECT_DOMAIN}/api` |\n300: | Production | `https://api.{PROJECT_DOMAIN}/api` |\n301: \n302: ---\n303: \n304: ## Authentication Flow\n305: \n306: - JWT via httpOnly cookies (NEVER localStorage)\n307: - Access Token: 1 hour expiry\n308: - Refresh Token: 7 days expiry\n309: - Cookie config: `httpOnly: true, secure: true, sameSite: 'strict'`\n310: \n311: ---\n312: \n313: ## Development Conventions\n314: \n315: ### Naming Conventions\n316: \n317: | Element | Convention | Example |\n318: |---------|------------|---------|\n319: | Components | PascalCase | `UserProfile.tsx` |\n320: | Shadcn/UI | lowercase | `button.tsx`, `card.tsx` |\n321: | Pages | PascalCase | `LoginPage.tsx` |\n322: | Services | camelCase + Service | `userService.ts` |\n323: | Redux slices | camelCase + Slice | `userSlice.ts` |\n324: | Types | `.d.ts` per domain | `user.d.ts` |\n325: | Entities | kebab-case | `user.entity.ts` |\n326: | DTOs | PascalCase | `CreateUserDto` |\n327: | Enums | kebab-case + .enum | `role.enum.ts` |\n328: | Routes | kebab-case | `auth.routes.ts` |\n329: \n330: ### Import Rules (Frontend)\n331: \n332: - Use `~/` alias for ALL imports (NOT `@/`, NOT relative paths like `../../`)\n333: - All imports use single quotes\n334: - Import order:\n335:   1. React and React-related\n336:   2. Third-party libraries\n337:   3. Redux hooks and actions\n338:   4. Enums\n339:   5. Components\n340:   6. Utilities\n341:   7. Type imports (grouped with `import type`)\n342:   8. Relative imports (same feature only)\n343: \n344: ### TypeScript Guidelines\n345: \n346: - Strict mode enabled — no implicit `any`, strict null checks\n347: - Use `import type` for type-only imports\n348: - Use `unknown` over `any` — add type guards to narrow\n349: - Props interfaces: defined separately, with JSDoc, PascalCase + `Props` suffix\n350: \n351: ---\n352: \n353: ## Design System\n354: \n355: ### Primary Color\n356: - **{PRIMARY_COLOR_NAME}**: {PRIMARY_COLOR_HEX}\n357: \n358: ---\n359: \n360: ## Available Commands\n361: \n362: | Command | Description |\n363: |---------|-------------|\n364: | `/commit` | Smart git commit with branch and PR management |\n365: | `/pull` | Pull latest changes for all submodules |\n366: | `/fullstack <project>` | Build any product from idea to deployment with infinite iteration loops |\n367: | `/new-project <name>` | Create complete new project with Claude config |\n368: \n369: ---\n370: \n371: ## Enabled MCP Servers\n372: \n373: - **sequential-thinking** - Step-by-step reasoning\n374: - **playwright** - Browser automation and E2E testing\n375: \n376: ---\n377: \n378: *Last Updated: {DATE}*\n\n(End of file - total 378 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# {PROJECT_NAME} - Project Configuration\n\n## Overview\n\n**Project**: {PROJECT_NAME}\n**Type**: {PROJECT_TYPE}\n**Status**: Development\n**Version**: 1.0\n\n{PROJECT_DESCRIPTION}\n\n**Key Differentiator**: {KEY_DIFFERENTIATOR}\n\n---\n\n## Behavioral Guidelines\n\nBehavioral guidelines to reduce common LLM coding mistakes. These guidelines bias toward caution over speed. For trivial tasks, use judgment.\n\n### 1. Think Before Coding","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude/templates/claude.template.md","time":{"start":1779165978571,"end":1779165978872}},"id":"prt_e3e8e59940013Ja6fx3ge90KL0","sessionID":"ses_1c171d1faffewtyKt5Yya44gpR","messageID":"msg_e3e8e32c4001nJqfzttzpjkH0T"}}
