{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779166042381,"sessionID":"ses_1c171d1faffewtyKt5Yya44gpR","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_00_C4t9QvlZLhRGluXytg2a6935","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/pipeline/phases/01-init.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/pipeline/phases/01-init.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Phase 1: Init (Project Scaffolding)\n2: \n3: Phase 1 sets up the target project directory, bootstraps `.claude/` configuration, scaffolds the directory structure, and generates directory-scoped rule files. After this phase, the project has a working skeleton ready for code generation.\n4: \n5: ## Prerequisites\n6: \n7: - Phase 0 (spec) complete, or `--skip-spec` used\n8: \n9: ## Execution\n10: \n11: ### Step 1.1: Resolve Target Project Directory\n12: \n13: ```\n14: IF --path is provided:\n15:   1. TARGET_DIR = resolve to absolute path (e.g., /Users/.../projects/tirebank)\n16:   2. Verify TARGET_DIR exists -> if not, mkdir -p TARGET_DIR\n17:   3. ALL file operations below use TARGET_DIR as root (not cwd)\n18:      - Status file:   TARGET_DIR/.claude-project/status/{project}/PIPELINE_STATUS.md\n19:      - PRD:           TARGET_DIR/.claude-project/prd/\n20:      - Skills/agents: still read from cwd's .claude/ (the source project)\n21:      - Code output:   TARGET_DIR/backend/, TARGET_DIR/frontend/, etc.\n22:   4. If --prd path is relative, resolve it from cwd (not TARGET_DIR)\n23: ELSE:\n24:   TARGET_DIR = cwd (current behavior, no change)\n25: ```\n26: \n27: **Key principle:** `.claude/` (commands, skills, agents) is read from the **source project** (where you run the command). All generated output goes to **TARGET_DIR**.\n28: \n29: ### Step 1.2: Bootstrap .claude in Target Project\n30: \n31: During Phase 1 (init), if `--path` was used and TARGET_DIR has no `.claude/`:\n32: \n33: ```bash\n34: cd TARGET_DIR\n35: git init  # if not already a git repo\n36: git submodule add -b main https://github.com/potentialInc/claude-fullstack.git .claude\n37: git submodule update --init --recursive\n38: ```\n39: \n40: This ensures the target project becomes self-sufficient -- after the first run, it has its own `.claude` and can run `/fullstack` natively.\n41: \n42: ### Step 1.3: Generate Directory-Scoped Rule Files\n43: \n44: After scaffolding directories, generate `.claude-rules` files from stack-specific templates. Each tech-stack submodule owns its own rule template, keeping rules accurate per framework.\n45: \n46: ```\n47: RULE FILE SOURCES (read from stack submodules):\n48:   Common:   .claude/templates/rules/common.claude-rules.template  -> TARGET_DIR/.claude-rules\n49:   Backend:  .claude/$BACKEND/templates/backend.claude-rules.template -> TARGET_DIR/backend/.claude-rules\n50:   Frontend: .claude/$FRONTEND/templates/frontend.claude-rules.template -> TARGET_DIR/frontend/.claude-rules\n51: ```\n52: \n53: ```bash\n54: # 1. Common rules (from claude-fullstack -- stack-agnostic)\n55: COMMON_TMPL=\".claude/templates/rules/common.claude-rules.template\"\n56: if [ -f \"$COMMON_TMPL\" ]; then\n57:   sed -e \"s/{PROJECT_NAME}/$PROJECT_NAME/g\" \\\n58:       -e \"s/{BACKEND}/$BACKEND/g\" \\\n59:       -e \"s/{FRONTEND}/$FRONTEND/g\" \\\n60:       \"$COMMON_TMPL\" > \"$TARGET_DIR/.claude-rules\"\n61: fi\n62: \n63: # 2. Backend rules (from $BACKEND stack submodule -- e.g., nestjs, django)\n64: BACKEND_TMPL=\".claude/$BACKEND/templates/backend.claude-rules.template\"\n65: if [ -f \"$BACKEND_TMPL\" ] && [ -d \"$TARGET_DIR/backend\" ]; then\n66:   sed -e \"s/{PROJECT_NAME}/$PROJECT_NAME/g\" \\\n67:       -e \"s/{BACKEND}/$BACKEND/g\" \\\n68:       \"$BACKEND_TMPL\" > \"$TARGET_DIR/backend/.claude-rules\"\n69: fi\n70: \n71: # 3. Frontend rules (from $FRONTEND stack submodule -- e.g., react, react-native)\n72: FRONTEND_TMPL=\".claude/$FRONTEND/templates/frontend.claude-rules.template\"\n73: if [ -f \"$FRONTEND_TMPL\" ]; then\n74:   # Auto-detect frontend directory name\n75:   for candidate in frontend frontend-web web client app; do\n76:     if [ -d \"$TARGET_DIR/$candidate\" ]; then\n77:       sed -e \"s/{PROJECT_NAME}/$PROJECT_NAME/g\" \\\n78:           -e \"s/{FRONTEND}/$FRONTEND/g\" \\\n79:           \"$FRONTEND_TMPL\" > \"$TARGET_DIR/$candidate/.claude-rules\"\n80:       break\n81:     fi\n82:   done\n83: fi\n84: ```\n85: \n86: ### Stack Submodule Ownership Table\n87: \n88: | Stack            | Template Location                                       | Target                    |\n89: | ---------------- | ------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------- |\n90: | claude-fullstack | `templates/rules/common.claude-rules.template`          | `/.claude-rules`          |\n91: | nestjs           | `nestjs/templates/backend.claude-rules.template`        | `/backend/.claude-rules`  |\n92: | django           | `django/templates/backend.claude-rules.template`        | `/backend/.claude-rules`  |\n93: | react            | `react/templates/frontend.claude-rules.template`        | `/frontend/.claude-rules` |\n94: | react-native     | `react-native/templates/frontend.claude-rules.template` | `/frontend/.claude-rules` |\n95: \n96: This way, when a new stack is added (e.g., `claude-django`), it brings its own rule template -- no changes needed in claude-fullstack.\n97: \n98: ### Step 1.4: Create Status File\n99: \n100: ```\n101: Status file path: {TARGET_DIR}/.claude-project/status/{project}/PIPELINE_STATUS.md\n102: \n103: If status file doesn't exist:\n104: 1. Copy template from .claude/templates/PIPELINE_STATUS.template.md (read from source cwd)\n105: 2. Replace {PROJECT_NAME} with actual project name\n106: 3. Set all phases to Pending status\n107: 4. Set generation: 1\n108: 5. Write to {TARGET_DIR}/.claude-project/status/{project}/\n109: ```\n110: \n111: ### Step 1.5: Resolve and Validate Tech Stack\n112: \n113: ```\n114: 1. Read the tech_stack section from PIPELINE_STATUS.md:\n115:    tech_stack:\n116:      backend: nestjs          # or django\n117:      frontends: [react]       # one or more\n118:      dashboards: [admin]      # optional\n119: \n120: 2. Set variables:\n121:    - $BACKEND = tech_stack.backend\n122:    - $FRONTEND = tech_stack.frontends[0] (primary)\n123: \n124: 3. Validate required submodules exist:\n125:    For backend and each frontend, check .claude/$STACK/ directory exists.\n126:    If missing, report install instructions and stop.\n127: \n128: 4. Resolve skill paths for all phases (see skill path table below).\n129: ```\n130: \n131: ### Step 1.6: Generate CLAUDE.md (MANDATORY)\n132: \n133: CLAUDE.md is the project's primary configuration file — it tells Claude Code about the tech stack, coding patterns, doc reading requirements, and anti-patterns. It MUST exist before any code phase runs.\n134: \n135: ```\n136: 1. Read template: .claude/templates/claude.template.md\n137: \n138: 2. Replace ALL placeholders using resolved values from Step 1.5:\n139: \n140:    Project:\n141:    - {PROJECT_NAME}         → project name\n142:    - {PROJECT_TYPE}         → \"Fullstack Web Application\"\n143:    - {PROJECT_DESCRIPTION}  → from seed.goal or PRD overview (if available), else \"TODO\"\n144:    - {KEY_DIFFERENTIATOR}   → from seed or PRD, else \"TODO\"\n145:    - {PROJECT_DOMAIN}       → from seed or PRD (e.g., \"taskboard.com\"), else \"{PROJECT_NAME}.com\"\n146:    - {DATE}                 → current date (YYYY-MM-DD)\n147: \n148:    Tech Stack:\n149:    - {BACKEND}              → tech_stack.backend (e.g., \"nestjs\")\n150:    - {FRONTEND}             → tech_stack.frontends[0] (e.g., \"react\")\n151:    - {ADMIN_DASHBOARD}      → tech_stack.dashboards[0] or \"React (same app)\" or \"N/A\"\n152:    - {DATABASE}             → \"PostgreSQL\" (default)\n153:    - {ORM}                  → \"TypeORM\" (for nestjs) or \"Prisma\" (for django)\n154:    - {AUTH}                 → \"JWT httpOnly cookies\"\n155:    - {DEPLOYMENT}           → \"Docker\" (default)\n156: \n157:    Roles (from seed ontology or PRD user types):\n158:    - {ROLE_1}               → primary non-admin role name (e.g., \"Project Owner\")\n159:    - {ROLE_1_DESCRIPTION}   → role description from PRD\n160:    - {ROLE_1_PERMISSIONS}   → key permissions summary\n161:    - {ROLE_2}               → secondary role name (e.g., \"Team Member\")\n162:    - {ROLE_2_DESCRIPTION}   → role description from PRD\n163:    - {ROLE_2_PERMISSIONS}   → key permissions summary\n164:    - {ADMIN_PERMISSIONS}    → admin role permissions summary\n165:    - {ROLE_ENUM_VALUES}     → comma-separated enum values (e.g., \"`project_owner`, `team_member`, `admin`\")\n166: \n167:    Design:\n168:    - {PRIMARY_COLOR_NAME}   → from DESIGN_SYSTEM.md or PRD, else \"Blue\"\n169:    - {PRIMARY_COLOR_HEX}    → from DESIGN_SYSTEM.md or PRD, else \"#4A90D9\"\n170: \n171:    NOTE: If seed/PRD is not yet available (Phase 0 skipped, Phase 2 not run),\n172:    use \"TODO\" for description/role fields. Phase 2 will re-generate CLAUDE.md\n173:    with full values after PRD conversion.\n174: \n175: 3. Write to: {TARGET_DIR}/CLAUDE.md\n176: \n177: 4. Verify: CLAUDE.md exists and contains no remaining {PLACEHOLDER} tokens\n178:    bash: grep -cE '\\{[A-Z_]+\\}' {TARGET_DIR}/CLAUDE.md\n179:    Expected: 0 (all placeholders resolved)\n180:    If > 0: FAIL — unresolved placeholders found, fix before proceeding\n181: ```\n182: \n183: ### Skill Path Resolution Table\n184: \n185: ```\n186: Phase -> Tier -> Skill Path\n187: ---------------------------\n188: spec      -> ooo       -> .claude/spec/commands/ouroboros/interview.md + seed.md\n189: init      -> core      -> .claude/skills/operation/phase-1-init.md\n190: prd       -> core+back -> .claude/skills/dev/generate-prd/SKILL.md (generate)\n191:                        -> .claude/$BACKEND/guides/workflow-convert-prd-to-knowledge.md (convert)\n192: design    -> core      -> .claude/skills/design-orchestrator.md (orchestrator)\n193:                        -> .claude/skills/design-system-creator.md (3a)\n194:                        -> .claude/skills/design-prompts-generator.md (3b)\n195:                        -> .claude/skills/html-generator.md (3c)\n196:                        -> .claude/skills/design-qa-validator.md (3d)\n197: database  -> $BACKEND  -> .claude/$BACKEND/guides/workflow-design-database.md\n198: backend   -> $BACKEND  -> .claude/$BACKEND/skills/api-development/SKILL.md\n199: frontend  -> $FRONTEND -> .claude/$FRONTEND/skills/converters/html-to-react-converter.md\n200: integrate -> $FRONTEND -> .claude/$FRONTEND/skills/api-integration/SKILL.md\n201: test      -> $BACKEND  -> .claude/$BACKEND/guides/workflow-generate-e2e-tests.md (backend API tests)\n202:            + $FRONTEND -> .claude/$FRONTEND/skills/e2e-test-generator.md (frontend E2E tests)\n203: qa        -> $FRONTEND -> .claude/$FRONTEND/skills/qa/design-qa-html.md + qa/design-qa-figma.md\n204: ship      -> core      -> .claude/skills/deployment.md\n205: ```\n206: \n207: ## Quality Gate\n208: \n209: ```yaml\n210: gate: directories_exist AND status_file_created AND tech_stack_validated AND claude_md_generated\n211: checks:\n212:   - project_dir_exists: \"TARGET_DIR exists and is a git repo?\"\n213:   - claude_submodule: \".claude/ exists in TARGET_DIR (if --path used)?\"\n214:   - status_file: \"PIPELINE_STATUS.md created with all phases?\"\n215:   - rule_files: \".claude-rules files generated for common/backend/frontend?\"\n216:   - tech_stack_valid: \"Required submodules ($BACKEND, $FRONTEND) exist?\"\n217:   - claude_md: \"CLAUDE.md exists at TARGET_DIR root with no unresolved {PLACEHOLDER} tokens?\"\n218: ```\n219: \n220: ## Loop Integration\n221: \n222: - No loop workflow runs for this phase\n223: - Phase 1 is deterministic scaffolding only\n224: \n225: ---\n226: \n227: ## Phase Completion — Status Update (MANDATORY)\n228: \n229: **No gate script exists for this phase.** Status updates must be done manually via the blueprint's `update-pipeline-status` agentic node.\n230: \n231: Update `{TARGET_DIR}/.claude-project/status/{project}/PIPELINE_STATUS.md`:\n232: 1. Progress Table: Status, Score (from evaluation), Output\n233: 2. Execution Log: Append row\n234: 3. Config: Update `last_run`, recalculate `pipeline_score`\n\n(End of file - total 234 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Phase 1: Init (Project Scaffolding)\n\nPhase 1 sets up the target project directory, bootstraps `.claude/` configuration, scaffolds the directory structure, and generates directory-scoped rule files. After this phase, the project has a working skeleton ready for code generation.\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n- Phase 0 (spec) complete, or `--skip-spec` used\n\n## Execution\n\n### Step 1.1: Resolve Target Project Directory\n\n```\nIF --path is provided:\n  1. TARGET_DIR = resolve to absolute path (e.g., /Users/.../projects/tirebank)\n  2. Verify TARGET_DIR exists -> if not, mkdir -p TARGET_DIR\n  3. ALL file operations below use TARGET_DIR as root (not cwd)\n     - Status file:   TARGET_DIR/.claude-project/status/{project}/PIPELINE_STATUS.md\n     - PRD:           TARGET_DIR/.claude-project/prd/\n     - Skills/agents: still read from cwd's .claude/ (the source project)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude/pipeline/phases/01-init.md","time":{"start":1779166042078,"end":1779166042378}},"id":"prt_e3e8f51f3001SoTMtsBly0s2l6","sessionID":"ses_1c171d1faffewtyKt5Yya44gpR","messageID":"msg_e3e8f3494001ul3LEd2YNth1uL"}}
